column27:
Current implementation: user can enter an invalid transaction pin multiple times and keeps trying with no limit.



Solution:

* in the backend count the number of transaction PIN failed entries
* if the number reaches 3 then lock the account, email that they must contact support
* if they enter the correct PIN (and it’s not locked) then reset the count to 0



In transaction endpoint:

{code:java}int concurrentIncorrectPinEntries; (from DB)

if ( concurrentIncorrectPinEntries > 2 ) {
  send email to contact support
  return “locked, contact support”
} 
else if ( !pinIsCorrect ) {
  concurrentIncorrectPinEntries++;
  return "incorrect PIN"
}
else if ( pinIsCorrect ) {
  concurrentIncorrectPinEntries = 0
  continue processing request…
}{code}

